Cell.Text: Then the rest is up to me. | Are you ready to go? I'm not entirely sure what this thing is going to do when I add my blood.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabPortalBranchTopic: The ingredients are in the vessel.
DLC1VQ04RNPCLabPortalBranchTopic01: Can I ask you something first?

Cell.Text: I've been asking myself the same thing since we came back to the castle. | She was so sure of what we did to my father, I couldn't help but go along with her. I never thought of the cost.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabQuestionsBranchTopic: What will you do if we find your mother?

Cell.Text: [S] Possibly. I guess even a vampire mother is still a mother. | She worried about me. About all of us. But she wanted to get me as far away from my father as possible before he really went over the edge.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabQuestionsBranchTopic01a: It sounds like she did everything for your sake.

Cell.Text: [S] Neither do I. | She always seemed happy, before we heard the prophecy. Then it all changed. She became a different person. They both did.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabQuestionsBranchTopic01b: I don't know what she was thinking.

Cell.Text: [S] She wasn't, always. But I think you're right. | She was practically smirking as we left home. Almost like she was proud of herself. | Like she didn't want to just stop my father... she wanted to stick it to him, too.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabQuestionsBranchTopic01c: It sounds like she was pretty selfish.

Cell.Text: Yes... yes, you're right. I'm sorry. I just didn't expect anyone to care how I felt about her. Thank you. | Are we ready then?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLabQuestionsEndBranchTopic: We won't know until we find her.
